<h2>Returns Procedure:</h2>
<p>To return a product you need to obtain a Return Merchandise Authorization (RMA) number. You need to apply for an RMA Request to return any incorrectly supplied/faulty or damaged items. <strong>NO returns of any type will be accepted without an RMA number. Please follow the simple procedure given below to apply for an RMA:</strong></p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>1. Login to your account using your email address and password.</p>
<p>2. Once logged in, click on the 'My account' tab in the main navigation.</p>
<p>3. Click on 'Order history' from the menu on the left. A list of previous orders will be displayed. Please click on the order to view order details. Click on the 'Need to return this product?' link to submit the RMA request.</p>
<p>4. A RMA request form will be displayed on screen. Please complete the form providing full information regarding the item in the comments box. You may complete the returns-form even though you may only be returning an individual component of the product.</p>
<p>5. Submit the form. Upon submission a unique RMA reference number will be issued to you. Please note this number down as you may require it for future correspondence. An email confirmation will also follow with the RMA details.</p>
<p>6. To prevent any confusion, we do not ship out any replacements until the goods have been received back to our warehouse for returns-processing. However if faulty goods have been received and replacements are urgent then we may arrange to ship out a replacement product (if in stock). Please note for such scenarios the customer will be required to pay the full amount for the replacement goods whilst the faulty product is on its way to us, and upon receipt of the faulty product a full refund will be passed for the new amount paid.</p>
<p>7. Your request is sent to our Returns Team who will then reply by e-mail and inform you of the outcome.</p>
<p>8. PLEASE DO NOT SEND THE GOODS BEFORE AN ACCEPTANCE EMAIL HAS BEEN RECEIVED (WHICH WILL CONTAIN ADDITIONAL INFORMATION REGARDING YOUR RETURN) TO AVOID ADDITIONAL CHARGES IN THE EVENT OF REJECTION.</p>
